Print method for shapr objects

Source: R/print.R
print.shapr.Rd

Print method for shapr objects

Usage

# S3 method for class 'shapr'
print(
  x,
  what = c("shapley_est", "shapley_sd", "MSEv", "MSEv_explicand", "MSEv_coalition",
    "timing_summary"),
  digits = 4,
  nsmall = max(0, digits - 2),
  ...
)

Arguments

x

A shapr object

what

Character. Which component to print. Options are "shapley_est", "shapley_sd", "MSEv", "MSEv_explicand", "MSEv_coalition", and "timing_summary. Defaults to "shapley_est". Only one component can be printed at a time. See the details section of get_results() for details about each component.

digits

Integer. Number of significant digits to display. Defaults to 4.

nsmall

Integer. Minimum digits to the right of the decimal point. Defaults to 2 less than digits.

...

Further arguments passed to data.table::print.data.table().

Value

The object is returned invisibly after printing selected output.
